peopleAlsoAsk.question: Where is the mint mark on a 1927 buffalo nickel?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: On the Buffalo Nickel, the mint mark is on the coin's reverse side, below the denomination "FIVE CENTS." The coin's obverse features a striking portrait of a Native American chief facing to the right, adorned with feathers in his hair.
